ITEM 2.02. RESULTS OF OPERATIONS AND FINANCIAL CONDITION.
On October 16, 2008, the Registrant issued a press release announcing results of operations for third quarter 2008 for The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation. A copy of this press release is filed as Exhibit 99.1 to this report and is incorporated herein by reference. However, the references in the press release to the Registrant's website, , shall not be deemed to include the contents of the website in the press release or in this Form 8-K. The information included herein is to be considered "filed" under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and is incorporated by reference into all filings made by the Registrant under the Securities Act of 1933 and the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 which state that this Current Report on Form 8-K is incorporated therein by reference.
http://www.bnymellon.com/
ITEM 9.01. FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND EXHIBITS.
(d) EXHIBITS.
 
Pursuant to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, the Registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned thereunto duly authorized.
 
 

Exhibit 99.1
 
 
The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation (NYSE:BK) today reported income from continuing operations of $305 million, or $0.26 per share, in the third quarter of 2008. This compares to income from continuing operations of $642 million, or $0.56 per share, in the third quarter of 2007 and $302 million, or $0.26 per share, in the second quarter of 2008.
NEW YORK, October 16, 2008 
"In the face of unprecedented market volatility our operating performance exceeded expectations, driven by the strength and diversity of our securities servicing and asset management businesses. We supported our clients in these extraordinarily turbulent markets and I am very proud of the tireless dedication and focus of our employees," said Robert P. Kelly, chairman and chief executive officer of The Bank of New York Mellon.
"We recently announced our participation in the U.S. Treasury's program to invest capital in nine leading U.S. financial institutions. In addition, we are honored to have been selected by the Treasury as the sole provider of a broad range of custodial and trustee services for the government's Troubled Asset Relief Program (TARP)."
 
In the third quarter of 2008, the Company recorded an after-tax charge of $0.06 per share associated with merger and integration ("M&I") expenses and $0.03 per share related to the settlement with the IRS of tax structured lease transactions ("SILO/LILO"), as well as the settlement of several audit cycles. Additionally, in the third quarter of 2008, the Company recorded an after-tax charge of $0.37 per share, or $433 million, associated with various support agreements.
The operating results for the third quarter of 2008 also included pre-tax costs associated with the write-down of certain investment securities ($162 million). For additional information, see page 8.
(Unless otherwise noted, all comments begin with the results of the third quarter of 2008 and are compared to the third quarter of 2007). Please refer to the Quarterly Earnings Summary for detailed business segment information.
Third Quarter Highlights of The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation
