On February 1, 2011, The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation (the "Company") issued (i) $350,000,000 aggregate principal amount of the Company's 1.500% Senior Medium-Term Notes Series G due 2014 (the "3-Year Notes"), (ii) $500,000,000 aggregate principal amount of the Company's 4.150% Senior Medium-Term Notes Series G due 2021 (the "10-Year Notes") and (iii) $350,000,000 aggregate principal amount of the Company's Floating Rate Senior Medium-Term Notes Series G due 2014 (the "Floating Rate Notes", and together with the 3-Year Notes and the 10-Year Notes, the "Notes"). The Notes were registered under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, pursuant to a registration statement on Form S-3 (File No. 333-167832). In connection with this issuance, the legal opinion as to the legality of the Notes is being filed as Exhibit 5.1 to this report.
 
