ITEM 8.01. OTHER EVENTS.
On March 6, 2013, The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation (the "Company") issued (i) $300,000,000 aggregate principal amount of the Company's 0.700% Senior Medium-Term Notes Series G due 2016 (the "3-Year Fixed Rate Notes"), (ii) $300,000,000 aggregate principal amount of the Company's Floating Rate Senior Medium-Term Notes Series G due 2016 (the "3-Year Floating Rate Notes"), (iii) $600,000,000 aggregate principal amount of the Company's 1.350% Senior Medium-Term Notes Series G due 2018 (the "5-Year Fixed Rate Notes") and (iv) $300,000,000 aggregate principal amount of the Company's Floating Rate Senior Medium-Term Notes Series G due 2018 (the "5-Year Floating Rate Notes" and, together with the 3-Year Fixed Rate Notes, the 3-Year Floating Rate Notes and the 5-Year Fixed Rate Notes, the "Notes"). The Notes were registered under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, pursuant to a registration statement on Form S-3 (File No. 333-167832). In connection with this issuance, the legal opinion as to the legality of the Notes is being filed as Exhibit 5.1 to this report.
ITEM 9.01. FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND EXHIBITS.
